{{Infobox country | micronation = yes | conventional_long_name = KonungaRikerna Elgaland-Vargaland | common_name = Elgaland-Vargaland | status = Current | capital = | image_flag = Elgaland-Vargaland flag.png | image_coat = | symbol_type = | national_anthem = | image_map = <!--Government--> | leader_title1 = [[King]] | leader_name1 = [[Carl Michael von Hausswolff]] | leader_title2 = [[King]] | leader_name2 = [[Leif Elggren]] | government_type = [[Monarchy]] | area_km2 = | nummembers = 980 (2014)<ref name=nowandthen/> | established_event1 = Declared | established_date1 = May 27, 1992 | official_languages = [[English language|English]], [[Swedish language|Swedish]] | currency = | footnotes = }}
'''Elgaland-Vargaland''' is a [[conceptual art]] project<ref name=mass>{{cite web|url=http://www.massgallery.org/events/in-conversation-lief-elggren-and-cm-von-hausswolf/|title=In conversation: Leif Elggren and CM von Hausswolff|work=MASS Gallery|date=May 30, 2014|accessdate=June 22, 2016}}</ref> and [[micronation]] conceived and developed by [[Sweden|Swedish]] artists [[Carl Michael von Hausswolff]] and [[Leif Elggren]] in 1992. It is also known by its acronym "KREV"<ref name=mass/> (KonungaRikena Elgaland-Vargaland).
{{quote box|align=right|width=25%|bgcolor=#c6dbf7|quote="Elgaland-Vargaland is the largest – and most populous realm on Earth, incorporating all boundaries between other nations as well as Digital Territory and other states of existence. Every time you travel somewhere, and every time you enter another form, such as the dream state, you visit Elgaland-Vargaland."|source=— elgaland-vargaland.org}}
==Origins== Von Hausswolff and Elggren formed the name out of their own names and define the country as being the [[border]]s of other countries. The decision to found the country and name themselves kings was in reaction to Sweden still having a monarchy.<ref name=venice>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/06/09/arts/design/09bien.html|title=At Venice Biennale, Artists Plant Flag for Their State (of Mind)|work=New York Times|last=Kennedy|first=Randy|date=June 9, 2007|accessdate=June 9, 2016}}</ref> The country was announced in an advert in ''[[Dagens Nyheter]]'' newspaper. It was announced on May 27, 1992.<ref name=exist>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=ThnYCQAAQBAJ&pg=PT221|title=An Atlas of Countries That Don't Exist: A compendium of fifty unrecognized and largely unnoticed states|last=Middleton|first=Nick|date=November 5, 2015|publisher=Pan Macmillan|page=221|accessdate=June 22, 2016|isbn=9781447295297}}</ref> Other Scandinavian artists have had micronations, such as [[Lars Vilks]]' [[Ladonia (micronation)|Ladonia]].<ref name=expressen/>
==Operations== {{quote box|align=right|width=25%|bgcolor=#c6dbf7|quote="Elgaland-Vargaland is an extended series of objects and performances concerning territorial ownership, the right to rule and the rights of individuals."|source=—Gallery 400<ref name=gallery400>{{cite web|url=http://gallery400.uic.edu/exhibitions/the-inauguration-of-the-consulate-general-for-the-kingdoms-of-elgaland-vargaland|title=The Inauguration of the Consulate General for the Kingdoms of Elgaland-Vargaland|date=November 27, 2007|accessdate=June 22, 2016|work=Gallery 400|publisher=University of Illinois at Chicago}}</ref>}} Elgaland-Vargaland has a flag<ref name=nowandthen/> and national anthem, issues passports and stamps on request, and has had a number of "embassies" (art exhibitions).<ref name=venice/> Elggren often invokes "the image of a street-corner lunatic with a paper crown who declares himself King".<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=lN85AQAAIAAJ&q=elgaland&dq=elgaland|title=Micro-bionic: Radical Electronic Music and Sound Art in the 21st Century|first1=Thomas|last1=Bey|first2=William|last2=Bailey|publisher=Creation Books|date=2009|page=130}}</ref>
In March 1994, they opened a "general consulate" at [[Thomas Nordanstad Gallery]] in New York and applied for membership of the United Nations.<ref>{{cite journal|title=New Art Examiner|volume=25|issue=7-10|page=23|date=1998|publisher=New Art Association}}</ref> In 2002, on the tenth anniversary, a group of 10 travelled from Sweden to Estonia carrying only Elgaland-Vargaland passports - they were detained and their passports confiscated, and they were returned to Sweden the next day. They had planned to be turned away from each country in turn, indefinitely.<ref name=exist/> The same year, they released a musical album titled "The kingdoms of Elgaland-Vargaland, 1992-2002", published by Ash International.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kudosrecords.co.uk/release/ash6.6/various-artists-the-kingdoms-of-elgaland-vargaland.html|title=Various Artists, The Kingdoms of Elgaland Vargaland|work=Ash International|date=July 15, 2002}}</ref> In 2003, Elgaland-Vargaland attended a conference of micronations in Finland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.variant.org.uk/events/Market30/MM_Market.pdf|title=Between a Rock and a Hard Place – The Possibilities for Contemporary Art Institutions to Function as Critical Political Spaces|last=Muukkonen|first=Marita|date=2007|work=Variant.org.uk}}</ref>
As of 2007, the country had around 850 citizens<ref name=venice/> and by 2014 they claimed 980 citizens.<ref name=nowandthen>{{cite news|url=http://artforum.com/diary/id=46029|title=Now and Then|last=Yablonsky|first=Linda|date=March 31, 2014|work=Art Forum|accessdate=June 22, 2016}}</ref> In 2007 they had 20 ambassadors;<ref name=venice/> the embassy in Reykjavik opened in 1994 at the Nýlistasafninu (Museum of Fine Arts)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mbl.is/greinasafn/grein/131237/|title=Konungsríkin Elgaland - Vargaland|work=Morgunbladid|date=March 26, 1994|accessdate=June 22, 2016}}</ref> the embassy in Berlin was opened in 2006 at the [[Haus der Kulturen der Welt]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hkw.de/en/programm/projekte/veranstaltung/p_13838.php|title=The Opening of the Embassy of the Kingdom of Elgaland-Vargaland|work=HKW|date=October 21, 2006|accessdate=June 22, 2016}}</ref> and the Moroccan embassy opened in 2014 before the [[Marrakech Biennale]].<ref name=nowandthen/> A "Consulate General" was held at [[Gallery 400]] in Chicago for two months in 2007-8 as part of the city's Festival of Maps.<ref name=gallery400/> They have a number of Ministers, mainly artists, including trumpeter Greg Kelley who is Minister of Fanfares.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://gapersblock.com/transmission/2011/11/16/a_curious_of_crowns_leif_elggren_at_lampo/|title=A Curious of Crowns: Leif Elggren at Lampo|work=Transmission|publisher=Gapers Block|date=November 16, 2011|last=Sienko|first=Chris|accessdate=June 22, 2016}}</ref>
The claims extend to other "interstitial territories" such as the transition from being asleep to wakefulness (the hypnogogic state),<ref name=mass/> and [[limbo]]<ref name=exist/> and they also regard all dead people as being citizens. In 2007, they declared at the [[Venice Biennale]] that they had annexed the [[Isola di San Michele]], an island cemetery.<ref name=venice/> This annexation project appeared at the Gallery Niklas Belenius in 2008.<ref name=expressen>{{cite news|url=http://www.expressen.se/kultur/konst/elgaland-vargaland--galleri-niklas-belenius/|title=Elgaland-Vargaland / Galleri Niklas Belenius|work=Expressen|date=March 12, 2008|accessdate=June 22, 2016}}</ref>
==Reception== KREV has been described as an art project that criticises the principles of the nation state and von Hausswolff and Elggren has, with the projects hierarchical diagram, clearly stated their disgust towards any kind of racism, fascism and oligarchy.
