{{Infobox musical composition | name = Symphony No.&nbsp;6 | subtitle =''From a New Zealand Diary'' | type = | composer = {{nowrap|[[Aulis Sallinen]]}} | image = | caption = | border = Yes | movements = 4 | dedication = | key = | catalogue = [[Opus number|Op.]]&nbsp;65 | composed = {{start date|1989}}–90 | duration = Approx. 40 minutes | premiere_date = {{start date|1990|09|06|df=y}} | premiere_location = [[Napier, New Zealand|Napier]], New Zealand | premiere_conductor = [[Okko Kamu]] | premiere_performers = [[New Zealand Symphony Orchestra]] }}
The '''Symphony No.&nbsp;6''', '''''From a New Zealand Diary''''', [[Opus number|Op]].&nbsp;65, is an orchestral composition by the Finnish composer [[Aulis Sallinen]], who wrote the piece from 1989–90. The [[New Zealand Symphony Orchestra]], the commissioning institution, premiered the work on 6&nbsp;September 1990 in [[Napier, New Zealand|Napier]], under the baton of Sallinen's longtime advocate, [[Okko Kamu]]. Sallinen and his wife had vacationed in New Zealand the year prior, providing the composer with inspiration for the symphony, which—though properly symphonic in scope and in structure—has been described as involving "tone painting"; indeed, each of the four movements contains a descriptive title, unusual for a Sallinen symphony.
== Instrumentation == According to the publisher, [http://www.musicsalesclassical.com/composer/work/7940 Novello & Co], Symphony No.&nbsp;6 is scored for the following: *'''[[Woodwind section|Woodwind]]''': 3&nbsp;[[flute]]s (2&nbsp;doubling [[piccolo]]), 3&nbsp;[[oboe]]s (1&nbsp;doubling [[cor anglais]]), 3&nbsp;[[clarinet]]s in B{{music|flat}} (1&nbsp;doubling E{{music|flat}} clarinet, 1&nbsp;doubling B{{music|flat}} [[bass clarinet]]), 3&nbsp;[[bassoon]]s (1&nbsp;doubling [[contrabassoon]]) *'''[[Brass section|Brass]]''': 4&nbsp;[[French horn|horn]]s in F, 3&nbsp;[[trumpet]]s in B{{music|flat}}, 3&nbsp;[[trombone]]s, 1&nbsp;[[tuba]] *'''[[Percussion section|Percussion]]''': [[timpani]], percussionists (individual instruments?) *'''[[String section|String]]s''': [[violin]]s, [[viola]]s, [[cello]]s, [[double bass]]es, [[harp]], [[celesta]]
== Structure == The symphony is in four movements: # The Islands of the Sounds. The Sounds of the Islands (''attacca'') # Air, Rain # Kyeburn Diggings (''attacca'') # Finale, "Simply by sailing in a new direction / You could enlarge the world" ([[Allen Curnow]])
== Recordings == To date, Symphony No.&nbsp;6 has received two recordings, the first of which is from 1992 with Okko Kamu conducting the Malmö Symphony Orchestra on the [[BIS Records|BIS]] label. Finnish conductor [[:fi:Ari Rasilainen|Ari Rasilainen]] has also recorded the symphony as part of [[Classic Produktion Osnabrück|cpo's]] compendium of Sallinen's orchestral works. The Sixth Symphony joins the [[Cello Concerto (Sallinen)|Cello Concerto]] (Op.&nbsp;44, 1977) on the final volume of the cpo series.
